        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 22— 1882</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I now send two other drawings to be engraved, and please to attend to the following instructions.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Both drawings to be reduced to <formula><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></formula> of present scale.</p>
                    <p>They are to stand as shown by the pencil bounding square   They are highly magnified sections, therefore all the lines must be very fine.</p>
<p>You will see that in fig. 1 that some of the cells in the space marked c contain many rounded granules &amp; these must be attended to in the cuts. These are closer together in the long cells marked b.</p>
<p>In the exterior cells marked d, and in the cut-off root-hairs, marked e the granules are to be omitted as I have written down.</p>
<p>The tubes or ducts marked a are crossed by fine transverse lines.</p>
<p>The same remarks apply to fig 2, but here the granules, &amp; small spheres and elongated masses in the cells d and in the root hairs <hi rend="underline">e</hi> are to be carefully shown.</p>
                    <p>The letters <hi rend="underline">a</hi>, <hi rend="underline">b</hi>, <hi rend="underline">c</hi>, <hi rend="underline">d</hi>, <hi rend="underline">e</hi> are to be engraved in both figs. where now placed   The blocks had better be sent to me when drawn; and I particularly beg you to have them done as soon as possible</p>
<p>My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
